# Git — default branch and Linear work

- **Do not** implement features, fixes, or refactors directly on `main` unless the user **explicitly** says to work on `main` (e.g. “do this on main”, “commit to main”).
- For work tied to a Linear issue, create or use a **feature branch** named from the issue, e.g. `lin-34-short-description` or match the issue’s suggested git branch name when available.
- Start new work by branching from an up-to-date `main` (or the agreed base), not by committing unreviewed changes on `main`.
- If you discover uncommitted work on `main`, move it to a feature branch (checkout `-b`, commit there) so `main` stays clean unless the user says otherwise.
